!!【柯林斯英汉双解大词典】

:<div>

chalk /tʃɔːk/

(chalking,chalked,chalks) 

1. N-UNCOUNT Chalk is a type of soft, white rock. You can use small pieces of it for writing or drawing with. 白垩 

例： ...white cliffs made of chalk. …白垩绝壁。 

2. N-UNCOUNT Chalk is small sticks of chalk, or a substance similar to chalk, used for writing or drawing with. 粉笔 [also N in pl] 

例： ...somebody writing with a piece of chalk. …正用粉笔写字的某人。 

3. V-T If you chalk something, you draw or write it using a piece of chalk. 用粉笔画; 用粉笔写 

例： He chalked the message on the blackboard. 他用粉笔把这条消息写在黑板上。

</div>

